Last Friday we officially launched The Dr Helen Allergy Center Ringwood. Allergy, eczema, asthma and more under one roof.  We had so much support.  The feedback on the services, space and expert team has been amazing (more team to introduce...!). Our training room is named Sadie's Room, after Sadie Bristow and her legacy.  This is a community space for anyone to use.  We can provide anaphylaxis awareness training, targeted talks, demostrations and so much more.  We have already held food immunotherapy sessions here and allergen introduction clinics. Thank you so much and I'll try to tag some of our supporters @allergypenpals @sadiebristowfoundation @vitalitedairyfree @moofreechocolates @thedairyfreemum @inhalertailor @creativenaturesuperfoods @scratchsleeves @hello.grow.with.iris  @kittmedical @larocheposay @equaleats @biogaiaofficial @allergylifestyle  @childrensdietitian and so many more.  I can't tag them all.  They are allergy allies and we are so proud to champion them.  There are so many I cant tag so Im sorry if I missed you out. Lot's of exciting things coming... watch this space.  Our flaship allergy center is a huge space dedicated to all things allergy.  Diagnosis, testing, treatments (OIT and environmental allergies), eczema diagnosis and management, asthma diagnosis, testing, reviews, lightening the mental burdens and providing light to the community.  We are stronger together, and here to support you and your family in any way we can. How can I help you?  #allergy #clinic #launch #allergic #allergycheck #allergymom #allergymum #allergydad ##

I haven't stopped thinking about the tragic case of George Cadman-Ithell and his family this week, or any of the allergy tragedies which seem to happen all too often lately. Sadly, it now seems like George may have inadvertently worsened the severity of his reaction by running home during it to retrieve his EpiPens. This is in no way victim blaming but it is clear that many people aren't aware of co-factors such as exercise which can worsen anaphylaxis. Other cofactors include illness, alcohol, asthma and fatigue. But the other key factor is that too many allergy tragedies happen as a result of the victim not having their EpiPen to hand, usually wrongly assuming they have a 'mild' allergy having never suffered extreme reactions before. All people who have been prescribed EpiPens or Jext should ALWAYS carry both of them at all times to ensure they have prompt access to the treatment which is very safe and effective when given. Severe reactions can happen at any time, often when you least expect it. My heart goes out to George and his family, but I am so grateful to his mum for sharing his story to help raise awareness. #allergy #allergyawareness #anaphylaxis #allergymum #allergymom #foodallergy #epipen #allergies #ConSantanderConecto

Adrenaline pens NEED to be used immediately if you’re having a severe allergic reaction. Movement is a co-factor - it worsens symptoms of anaphylaxis like your airway closing up, dizziness, sickness and loss of consciousness. But when George accidentally ate something that contained nuts and realised he didn’t have his pens on him, he ran 8 minutes home. By the time his mum got there, paramedics were desperately trying to resuscitate him. George now lies in a vegetative state in hospital, two months on from his anaphylactic reaction. But as I write this, I’m a huge hypocrite. Just like George, I was diagnosed at 5 years old with severe nut allergies. Just like George, I’ve thankfully never needed to use my adrenaline pens. I normally carry them with me at all times, but when I got home from a long hike and lunch with friends on Saturday, I realised I had gone the entire day without my pens on me. I had a momentary panic before my girlfriend thankfully reminded me I was fine, nothing happened, and I’m home safe. But something could have happened… It’s just too easy to forget something so potentially life-saving. My heart goes out to George, his family, and his friends during this horribly difficult time. We need a better solution. #allergy #news #startup #founder #allergic #epipen #nutallergy #healthcare #medical #allergicreaction #firstaid
